Carrier Alerts\n3. Carrier Full Updates\n4. Carrier Sync\n    \n\nIn Addition to the four core components, Highway offers an OAuth 2.0 solution as well for allowing carriers to sign into your digital experience.\n\n**Pagination**\n\nHighway's API provides consistent handling of pagination for all collection responses. In your requests, you may use the following query params to control pagination:\n\n| **Query Param** | **Description** |\n| --- | --- |\n| page | The page number you want to view. Default is 1. |\n| per_page | Number of records per response. Default is 50 and max is 100. |\n\nHighway's API provides pagination information via the headers of the response. These headers and their description are listed below:\n\n| **Header** | **Description** |\n| --- | --- |\n| TotalItems | The total number of records the filters and/or query of your request matched. |\n| CurrentPage | The current page of the response. |\n| TotalPages | The total number of pages available based on the filters and/or query of your request. Accounts for the `per_page` value of your request. |",

						"description": "Users that have completed the Highway authentication and connection process will be redirected to a predefined URL set by you and your team. In that URL there will be an authorization code passed as a query param. Your system needs to be able to receive users to this URL, capture the authorization code, and trigger a `Create Access Token` API call to Highway.\n\nThis flow needs to happen in real-time as the user will be waiting for your system to handle these steps and send them on their user journey to your portal.\n\nIt's important to note, that when a user reaches this point, it means they have (1) authenticated to a carrier, (2) completed the connection process with you in Highway and (3) passed your rules assessment. Users that don't meet those three criteria will be held in Highway until they do.\n\nAfter receiving a successful `Create Access Token` response, your system needs to handle the following logic.\n\n*Step 1*\n\nIf the carrier does not exist in your system based on the `external_id` of the `connection` attribute in the response, then you need to create a new carrier by making a call to `Get an Onboarding Packet` and then proceed to Step 2.\n\n*Step 2*\n\nYou now should have a carrier saved in your system. This carrier's primary key in your system should match the `external_id` for this Highway connection. Next check if a user already exists with the email provided in the `user` attribute of this response. If a user does not exist, then create one and add the id provided by Highway for that user in your data storage for future reference.\n\n*Step 3*\n\nSign in the user to your portal or system. The access token is associated with a user, so each user in a company will have a different access token."

			"description": "#### Processing Carrier Alerts\n\nWhen a significant event occurs that might effect a brokers willingness to work with a carrier (ex. change in authority, insurance or anything that might impact a broker's rules for carriers), then Highway will generate a Carrier Alert. When a Carrier Alert is generated, the broker TMS needs to consume the carrier_detail object for the carrier which will ensure all data on the carrier in the broker TMS is up to date.\n\n**Process:**\n\n1. Broker TMS should set a cron job that runs \\~5 minutes and makes a GET request to the Alerts endpoint which includes an array of new alerts (with corresponding carrier_detail objects) in the response body.\n2. After processing and saving the alerts / carrier_detail objects, the broker TMS should make a POST request to the Mark Alerts As Processed endpoint so that Highway knows the alerts were successfully delivered."

This represents Interstate carrier and broker authority. |\n| Insurance | Insurance data on the carriers is broken into two parts: (1) data from the FMCSA L&I database and (2) from the carrier's insurance certificate. |\n| Lane Preferences | Lane activity for the carrier comes from historical data (inspection_areas), survey data (preferred_areas), and the location of their headquarters and terminals (headquarter_areas). |\n| Inspections | SMS recorded inspections over the last 24 months |\n| Safety | The carrier's safety rating from the FMCSA if they have one and their SMS BASICS scores |\n| Violations | SMS recorded violations over the last 24 months |\n| Crashes | SMS recorded crashes over the last 24 months |\n| Contact Information | Phones, email addresses, contacts, and addresses for the carrier are collected from a variety of sources. |\n| Certifications | A list of certifications associated with the carrier including verified and carrier provided. |\n| Specializations | A list of specializations that the carrier has represented through either a survey or onboarding packet |\n| Subscription | You are subscribed to alerts for this carrier. |"

						"description": "The Highway Onboarding Packet Consists of the following items:\n\n1. Basic Details\n2. Payment Term\n3. Payment Method\n4. Factor\n5. Executed Contracts\n6. Custom Questions\n7. Carrier Detail (this object is nested inside the onboarding_packet but can also be retrieved independently)\n    \n\n#### **Basic Details**\n\n1. **onboarding_packet.id** - Integer\n2. **onboarding_packet.status** - String\n    1. possible values:\n        1. \"incomplete\"\n        2. \"complete\"\n        3. \"held_for_carrier_approval\" - the onboarding packet was completed by a dispatcher and must be approved by the carrier before the status can be set to complete\n        4. \"held_for_incomplete_rules_assessment\" - the onboarding packet has been completed and approved by the carrier. However, there is not enough information to assess whether or not the carrier is passing the brokers rules. This happens when Highway has not been able to retrieve and validate the carrier's insurance certificate. As soon as the insurance certificate is obtained and processed, the onboarding packet status will be set to complete (if the carrier has adequate insurance) or will be set to held_for_failed_rules_assessment (if the carrier has inadequate insurance)\n        5. \"held_for_failed_rules_assessment\" - the onboarding packet has been completed and approved by the carrier. However, the carrier is failing the brokers rules. Before the status can be set to complete, the carrier must pass all the broker rules (or the broker must include a rule override for any failing rules)\n    2. Only completed onboarding packets should be consumed into your TMS\n        1. The GET Onboarding Packets (plural) request will only return completed onboarding packets\n        2. The GET Onboarding Packet (singular) can return any individual onboarding packet\n3. **onboarding_packet.created_at** - DateTime (from String)\n    \n\n#### Payment Term - Object\n\n**payment_term = onboarding_packet.payment_term**\n\n1. **payment_term.is_type** - String\n    1. possible_values\n        1. \"standard_pay\" - if selected:\n            1. the Discount Rate will be 0.0\n            2. the Days to Pay will be the standard number of days for this broker\n            3. There will be a Payment Method\n            4. Factor will be null\n        2. \"quick_pay\" - if selected:\n            1. there will be a Days to Pay that is less than the days to pay for standard pay\n            2. the Discount Rate will be greater than 0.0\n            3. There will be a Payment Method\n            4. Factor will be null\n        3. \"factoring\" - if selected:\n            1. the Days to Pay and Discount rate will be null because all payment details are decided between the carrier and factoring company\n            2. Payment Method will be null\n            3. There will be a Factor\n2. **payment_term.days_to_pay** - Integer\n3. **payment_term.discount_rate** -Decimal\n    1. This is the multiplier for the carrier discount on quick pays. Ex. A Discount Rate of 0.03 would be a 3% discount (the carrier would receive $97 on a $100 invoice)\n4. **payment_term.name** - String\n    \n\n#### Payment Method - Object\n\n**payment_method = onboarding_packet.payment_method**\n\n1. **payment_method.is_type** - String\n    1. possible values:\n        1. \"ach\" - when selected, the account_number and routing_number will be present; the address fields will be null\n        2. \"check\" - when selected, the applicable address fields will be present (ie street2 might be null, etc.); account_number and routing_number will be null\n2. **payment_method.street1** - String\n3. **payment_method.street2** - String\n4. **payment_method.city** - String\n5. **payment_method.state** - String\n6. **payment_method.postal_code** - String\n7. **payment_method.country** - String\n8. **payment_method.routing_number** - String\n9. **payment_method.account_number** - String\n    \n\n#### Factor - Object\n\n**factor = onboarding_packet.factor**\n\n1. **factor.name** - String\n2. **factor.triumph_pay_id** - String\n3. **factor.email_address** - String\n4. **factor.phone** - String\n5. **factor.mailing_address_street1** - String\n6. **factor.mailing_address_street2** - String\n7. **factor.mailing_address_city** - String\n8. **factor.mailing_address_state** - String\n9. **factor.mailing_address_postal_code** - String\n10. **factor.mailing_address_country** - String\n11. **factor.physical_address_street1** - String\n12. **factor.physical_address_street2** - String\n13. **factor.physical_address_city** - String\n14. **factor.physical_address_state** - String\n15. **factor.physical_address_postal_code** - String\n16. **factor.physical_address_country** - String\n    \n\n#### Executed Contracts - Array of of Executed Contract Objects\n\n**executed_contract = onboarding_packet.executed_contracts\\[n\\]**\n\n1. **executed_contract.is_type** - String\n    1. possible values:\n        1. \"broker_carrier_agreement\"\n        2. \"w9\"\n        3. null\n2. **executed_contract.signed_at** - DateTime (from String)\n3. **executed_contract.signed_by_id** - Integer\n4. **executed_contract.signed_by** - String\n5. **executed_contract.signed_by_email** - String\n6. **executed_contract.broker_uploaded** - Boolean\n7. **executed_contract.broker_uploaded_at** - DateTime (from String)\n8. **executed_contract.broker_uploaded_by_id** - Integer\n9. **executed_contract.broker_uploaded_by** - String\n10. **executed_contract.broker_uploaded_by_email** - String\n11. **executed_contract.file** - Object\n    1. **executed_contract.file.filename** - String\n    2. **executed_contract.file.content_type** - String\n        1. All contract files will be PDF (\"application/pdf\")\n    3. **executed_contract.file.url** - String\n        1. NOTE: the URL for each file will expire within 10 minutes of the initial API request to GET the onboarding packet (each request will generate a new URL)\n\n#### Custom Questions - Array of Custom Question Objects\n\n**custom_question = onboarding_packet.custom_questions\\[n\\]**\n\n1. **custom_question.question** - String\n2. **custom_question.description** - String\n3. **custom_question.answer** - String"
